 Kapil helps beat Pak in golf
Greater Noida: Kapil Dev made his golf debut for India as the hosts beat arch-rivals Pakistan 15.5-8.5 to lift their third successive Ravi Kirloskar Trophy on Friday. India dominated the final day of the tournament at the Jay Pee Greens Golf Course, suffering just four reversals in the single matches spread across various categories to emerge champions. Kapil competed in the 40-50 year age group and beat his rival Shuab-ud-Din 6-5. Two others in this category also registered wins but Col Ajay Singh lost to Shah Fakhar Imam to make it 3-1 in favour of India. India notched up three wins against a one loss in the national team category. (P TI) 
